536
00:46:58,870 --> 00:47:04,110
The right mindset comes from the right posture, right?

537
00:47:04,110 --> 00:47:09,130
What are they trying to do when these young people are weak?

538
00:47:32,460 --> 00:47:34,580
 Bae Seung Man

539
00:47:44,900 --> 00:47:47,060
I have to go to the bathroom.

540
00:48:17,350 --> 00:48:19,400
 Is it five minutes to 6 o'clock?

541
00:48:19,400 --> 00:48:24,910
 Look how crooked you are. Stand up straight!

542
00:48:34,840 --> 00:48:37,150
 Building a democratic welfare state that embodies a just society.

543
00:49:28,770 --> 00:49:32,270
Your order of two Americanos is ready.

544
00:49:35,430 --> 00:49:39,020
- Thank you. 
 - Goodbye.

545
00:49:42,870 --> 00:49:44,840
What's going on with Lee Jung Yeop? What is he doing?

546
00:49:44,840 --> 00:49:47,940
His mouth is closed tight. He's not even eating.

547
00:49:47,940 --> 00:49:51,940
We only have about an hour left at the most.

548
00:49:51,940 --> 00:49:55,770
Then don't we have to push him hard?

549
00:49:55,770 --> 00:50:01,330
I'm going crazy. I can't even look up the communication records because the warrant hasn't come through.

550
00:50:02,900 --> 00:50:04,450
What about his browsing history?

551
00:50:04,450 --> 00:50:07,880
It's a foreign portal site that doesn't use SNS.

552
00:50:07,880 --> 00:50:12,760
The site is mostly used by foreign companies. It looks like getting access will be tough.

553
00:50:21,880 --> 00:50:25,890
What about the hospital? Is there anything else from there? Anything on the patient medical records?

554
00:50:25,890 --> 00:50:30,110
Seonbae Geon Young was looking into that.

555
00:50:30,110 --> 00:50:33,250
Where did that jerk go?

556
00:50:33,250 --> 00:50:35,110
 Interrogation

557
00:50:36,530 --> 00:50:39,540
Hey! Where have you been?

558
00:50:39,540 --> 00:50:40,830
I went to go get some coffee.

559
00:50:40,830 --> 00:50:43,240
Coffee? This jerk really went by himself.

560
00:50:43,240 --> 00:50:49,070
It was for Lee Jung Yeop. He has luxurious tastes so he sent me to buy expensive coffee. He even made me buy two cups.

561
00:50:49,070 --> 00:50:53,810
- That's crazy. 
 - How despicable.

562
00:50:53,810 --> 00:50:58,030
Hold on. Did you say you bought two cups?

563
00:51:12,850 --> 00:51:15,230
What is he doing?

564
00:51:17,270 --> 00:51:19,810
I think he's giving an invitation?

565
00:51:23,890 --> 00:51:25,790
To whom?

566
00:51:39,350 --> 00:51:41,690
Your suit is nice.

567
00:51:44,450 --> 00:51:47,680
I'm Profiler Eugene Hathaway.

568
00:51:48,840 --> 00:51:50,510
That's unexpected.

569
00:51:50,510 --> 00:51:53,700
I was expecting someone more powerful.

570
00:51:53,700 --> 00:51:55,860
Are you disappointed?

571
00:51:56,720 --> 00:52:01,040
No. You were just different from what I expected.

572
00:52:02,030 --> 00:52:06,100
You are not a Korean police officer. For whom do you work?

573
00:52:06,100 --> 00:52:10,470
I'm with the United States Federal Bureau of Investigation. I was dispatched to the Central Police Agency.

574
00:52:10,470 --> 00:52:12,650
FBI?

575
00:52:17,510 --> 00:52:19,820
It's cold.

576
00:52:19,820 --> 00:52:22,830
You should have come earlier.

577
00:52:22,830 --> 00:52:25,590
Why, are you busy?

578
00:52:25,590 --> 00:52:28,740
I will be out of here in a little while.

579
00:52:28,740 --> 00:52:32,650
Yes, I know.

580
00:52:37,240 --> 00:52:39,990
You said your name is Eugene, right?

581
00:52:39,990 --> 00:52:44,690
Where are you from? Not your nationality, but your ethnicity.

582
00:52:44,690 --> 00:52:48,660
Are you Korean? Mixed race?

583
00:52:48,660 --> 00:52:50,520
Why do you want to know that?

584
00:52:50,520 --> 00:52:53,570
If you want to hear the truth, you also have to tell the truth.

585
00:52:53,570 --> 00:52:55,810
Building rapport. You should know it well.

586
00:52:55,810 --> 00:52:57,750
 Rapport - Intimacy or trust formed with the other party.

587
00:52:57,750 --> 00:52:59,510
What's going on?

588
00:52:59,510 --> 00:53:02,480
Why is he suddenly talking so much?

589
00:53:02,480 --> 00:53:04,990
Is it because he's in front of a woman?

590
00:53:12,270 --> 00:53:17,090
I was born in Korea and then adopted.

591
00:53:18,840 --> 00:53:21,070
Did you know?

592
00:53:25,180 --> 00:53:29,230
You were born in Korea and adopted, right?

593
00:53:30,020 --> 00:53:31,460
Do you have a question?

594
00:53:31,460 --> 00:53:33,780
What are your parents like?

595
00:53:33,780 --> 00:53:36,260
They were good people.

596
00:53:37,350 --> 00:53:40,350
They were good people.

597
00:53:40,350 --> 00:53:43,000
You're using the past tense. They're still alive.

598
00:53:43,000 --> 00:53:46,800
Why? Do you think I was abused?

599
00:53:47,500 --> 00:53:49,640
Why do you think that?

600
00:53:49,640 --> 00:53:51,800
Francis Bacon.

601
00:54:00,460 --> 00:54:03,490
Do you like contemporary art?

602
00:54:03,490 --> 00:54:10,320
This artist's work is not commonly seen in Korea. How did you get your hands on it?

603
00:54:10,320 --> 00:54:12,800
Did you buy it yourself?

604
00:54:12,800 --> 00:54:16,100
No. It was a gift.

605
00:54:17,740 --> 00:54:19,990
Why Francis Bacon of all artists?

606
00:54:19,990 --> 00:54:22,920
Some people don't like this artist.

607
00:54:24,770 --> 00:54:30,650
Just because I like grotesque paintings doesn't mean I had a twisted childhood.

608
00:54:30,650 --> 00:54:32,720
What was your childhood like?

609
00:54:32,720 --> 00:54:35,880
What are your parents like?

610
00:54:39,590 --> 00:54:41,810
Answer me.

611
00:54:41,810 --> 00:54:45,650
If you answer, then I will answer your questions.

612
00:55:05,870 --> 00:55:08,020
They were

613
00:55:09,320 --> 00:55:11,920
good people.

614
00:55:12,820 --> 00:55:14,640
You used the past tense.

615
00:55:14,640 --> 00:55:17,050
Why did you come to Korea?

616
00:55:18,500 --> 00:55:20,130
Because it was a good opportunity.

617
00:55:20,130 --> 00:55:22,780
Because in the UK, being a doctor is like being in public service.

618
00:55:22,780 --> 00:55:24,140
What about here?

619
00:55:24,140 --> 00:55:27,330
It's a job that makes money, and they're very well liked.

620
00:55:27,330 --> 00:55:30,630
Are you saying that Koreans are your money makers?

621
00:55:30,630 --> 00:55:32,540
You don't like Korea.

622
00:55:32,540 --> 00:55:34,600
Oh, do I have to like it?

623
00:55:34,600 --> 00:55:36,630
Do you like it?

624
00:55:37,650 --> 00:55:39,580
I try to understand.

625
00:55:39,580 --> 00:55:45,070
Understand? Liking something is in the area of emotions.

626
00:55:46,260 --> 00:55:48,050
Understanding is this side.

627
00:55:48,050 --> 00:55:50,060
To like is this side.

628
00:55:50,060 --> 00:55:52,610
These are completely different.

629
00:55:55,310 --> 00:55:59,370
Do you have a problem with this side?

630
00:56:00,780 --> 00:56:02,720
Are you analyzing me?

631
00:56:02,720 --> 00:56:06,650
Are you offended? I didn't mean to.

632
00:56:06,650 --> 00:56:11,540
I'm not offended, I'm disappointed.

633
00:56:11,540 --> 00:56:16,840
Lee Jung Yeop, you are more of a coward than I thought.

634
00:56:18,880 --> 00:56:21,430
Thank you for the coffee.

635
00:56:22,850 --> 00:56:24,770
Wait a minute.

636
00:56:26,330 --> 00:56:28,230
What do you want to say?

637
00:56:28,230 --> 00:56:32,080
If you call for me then talk. Don't mess around with me.

638
00:56:34,290 --> 00:56:37,260
What is important now?

639
00:56:39,490 --> 00:56:42,800
What do you need to know?

640
00:56:42,800 --> 00:56:45,180
Who the culprit is?

641
00:56:45,180 --> 00:56:50,150
No. What's really important is

642
00:56:51,500 --> 00:56:54,280
who's next.

643
00:56:57,880 --> 00:57:00,710
Are you warning us of the crime beforehand?

644
00:57:04,390 --> 00:57:09,240
Lee Jung Yeop. Are you the culprit?

645
00:57:12,480 --> 00:57:16,670
If you're not, do you know who the culprit is?

646
00:57:18,740 --> 00:57:20,680
No.

647
00:57:25,280 --> 00:57:30,320
You should not ask who did it but why they did it first.

648
00:57:32,470 --> 00:57:35,820
Nothing on this Earth just happens for no reason.

649
00:57:35,820 --> 00:57:42,390
It's memories that make us human, because everything that is happening now is a result of the past.

650
00:57:43,650 --> 00:57:45,710
The past?

651
00:57:45,710 --> 00:57:47,670
What past?

652
00:57:47,670 --> 00:57:49,890
Whose past?

653
00:57:59,170 --> 00:58:04,030
Who are you?

